      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your<strong> gluten free brioche bun[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Spread the <strong>cheesy garlic butter</strong> over the outside and inside of the<strong> sliced brioche</strong>, then add to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-7 min or until crusty – this is your<strong> garlic bread</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>mashed roasted garlic</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong> and your<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>roasted garlic aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
