            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then remove 1 <strong>outer leaf</strong> per person from your <strong>lettuce</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and set aside, then chop the inner core into quarters, lengthways</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the pan, season generously with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> then give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>pulled chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
